### Task Tags API Test File
### Make sure to replace {token} with a valid JWT token from authentication

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7000
@token = {your-jwt-token-here}

### 1. Get all tags
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 2. Create a new tag
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Urgent"
}

### 3. Create another tag
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bug"
}

### 4. Create a third tag
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Feature"
}

### 5. Get all tags again to see the created ones
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Create a task first (if you don't have one)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Task with Tags",
  "description": "This task will be used to test tag assignment",
  "priority": 1,
  "status": 0
}

### 7. Assign tags to a task (replace {taskId} with actual task ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

[1, 2, 3]

### 8. Assign different tags to the same task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

[1, 2]

### 9. Remove all tags from a task
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tasks/1/tags
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

[]

### 10. Delete a tag (only if not assigned to any tasks)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/tags/3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Try to delete a tag that's assigned to tasks (should fail)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/tags/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
